On 10/8/15, Razer <Rayzer@riseup.net> wrote:
>
> Show me the advantage over cooperating with others equilaterally.

universal cooperation is global optima -
 the trick is to pass from crude biological competitive roots
  into global egalitarianism through universal cooperation.

this is also known as solving the Fermi paradox,
  becoming the first species to pass through paradox proves it.

note that designing fully decentralized technology sufficient to
support this transition,
 regardless of the socio-economic difficulties retarding adoption of same,
  is sufficiently difficult as to be considered "impossible" by sane majorities.

